      "name": "CISA Advisory: Active Exploitation of Ivanti Connect Secure Zero-Day (CVE-2025-0282)",
      "description": "The Cybersecurity and Infrastructure Security Agency (CISA), together with NCSC-UK, is today warning of active exploitation of CVE-2025-0282, a critical stack-based buffer overflow in Ivanti Connect Secure VPN appliances allowing unauthenticated remote code execution. Intelligence indicates that multiple threat actors, including APT29 (Cozy Bear), are actively exploiting this vulnerability in the wild. Federal Civilian Executive Branch agencies are ordered to apply available mitigations within 48 hours. Organisations using Ivanti Connect Secure should immediately apply vendor patches, check for indicators of compromise using Ivanti's Integrity Checker Tool, and consider temporarily taking affected appliances offline if patching cannot be completed immediately.",
